oth sides &quot;Educator should be happy that there is one less child in their overcrowded classroom.&quot; Pretty much says you already think the teacher can't do the job anyway. I mean, when you're talking 30-40 kindergarters to a teacher yea that's too much, but hell when we were in school, most of my classes were about 25-30ish kids, with one teacher, and it seemed to go well. We didn't have the now so prevalent teacher's aides either. Sometimes it's good for children to learn within a less individualized setting. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="817" language="en" documentId="543" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="mamaKto2under2" date="09/05/2013" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://community.babycenter.com/post/a44369503/home_schooling_debate_this_hypothetical?cpg=18" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="543" notes="" title="Home schooling: Debate this hypothetical"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="272"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="273" end="817"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43"/></xmi:XMI>